ABOUT 100 pupils ate poisoned cookies on Thursday. 19 leaners are fighting for their lives in
hospital. The pupils were admitted to hospital on Thursday afternoon
after they allegedly ate space cookies. The Gauteng SAPS spokesman, Kay Makhubele told Daily Sun
that these learners are from Lufentse Girls High school in Orlando East, Soweto. "They were rushed to the Chris Hani Baragwanath
Academic hospital. The investigation is ongoing. More information will be communicated
in due cause," said Makhubele. Gauteng MEC for Education, Panyaza Lesufi also stated
that the department is still investigating the case. 